        "**(Question 1):** What is Simple Linear Regression (SLR)?\n",
        " Explain its purpose"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_jNWKeKhwzBN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "Simple Linear Regression (SLR) is a statistical method used to model the relationship between two variables by fitting a linear equation to observed data.\n",
        "\n",
        "One variable is considered the independent variable (predictor), and the other is the dependent variable (response). The purpose of SLR is to predict the value of the dependent variable based on the value of the independent variable and to understand the strength and direction of their relationship"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xwXCBVdyw-yd"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**(Question 2):** What are the key assumptions of Simple Linear Regression?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nECYipWLxRHl"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "The key assumptions of Simple Linear Regression are:\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   Linearity: The relationship between the independent and dependent variables is linear.\n",
        "2.   Independence: Observations are independent of each other.\n",
        "3.   Homoscedasticity: The variance of the residuals (errors) is constant across all levels of the independent variable.\n",
        "4.   Normality: The residuals are normally distributed.\n",
        "5.   No multicollinearity: In SLR, there is only one independent variable, so multicollinearity is not a concern"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zsAe2AtdxbKt"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**(Question 3):** Write the mathematical equation for a simple linear regression model and explain each term."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qh84Ba8jx4Wd"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Answer:**\n",
        "\n",
        "The equation for a simple linear regression model is: y = β₀ + β₁x + ε\n",
        "\n",
        "    Where:\n",
        "\n",
        "    y: Dependent variable (response variable).\n",
        "    x: Independent variable (predictor variable).\n",
        "    β₀: Intercept (value of y when x = 0).\n",
        "    β₁: Slope (rate of change in y for a unit change in x).\n",
        "    ε: Error term (difference between observed and predicted values).*italicised text*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MthAwspIyBlt"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
